{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"571ffd16-0cc8-485d-8f6c-f1804653e5f5","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // optional: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the assertion to the exact call.\n- You can inspect the exception object (message, inner exception, etc.).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8994094-558d-408d-94d3-f363b7f0cb29","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to search the codebase.","outputTokens":262,"requestId":"0429:1256A4:18CE185:1C2F184:69E820FF"},"id":"47e1cb7b-f2e4-4fae-b160-64ad27d65aad","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:14:45.416Z","parentId":"57841774-124b-490e-94c7-3a54c101f4ba"}
